When the planning unit changes form hours to days or vice versa, existing estimates are not converted. That is, when the planning unit is days and an item has an estimate of 1 (interpreted as 1d) it will still have an estimate of 1 after changing the planning unit to hours. However, now its estimate will be interpreted as 1h which means that the estimation has changed from 8h to 1h. In order to prevent users from manually adapting existing estimates when changing the planning unit, they should automatically transformed to the new unit. That means that in the above example the item's estimate would change to 8. This way the estimate of the item would remain unchanged.

